creator: Seafood City Supermarket
descriptionHtml: They say home is where the heart is. Nobody knows this better than the Filipino-Americans. In the 1960s, the first wave of Filipinos came to America. With their arrival began the struggle to find products that were sariling atin, meaning “truly ours.” Back then, Filipino-Americans would wander into Asian grocery stores looking for anything familiar. Now, the words ‘Seafood City’ have become synonymous with ‘home,’ ‘community.’ And nowhere is true Filipino goodness better celebrated than here.
descriptionShort: They say home is where the heart is. Find the true Filipino goodness here.
